Actions.

Use actions when you want to know what special things you can try in your
current room.

This is useful for screenreader users because some room details are hidden in
descriptions, signs, objects, or local commands. Actions summarizes the most
important exploration hooks in one place.

Common forms:

actions
  List special actions, things to look at, and things to read in the room.

interact
roomactions
readables
  Other names for the same command.

The output may include lines like:

Actions here are "pull", "search", "touch", and "travel".

Things to look at here are "altar", "pillar", and "markings".

Things to read here are "read sign" and "read inscription".

Actions are commands you can type directly. Things to look at are room details
you can inspect with look, for example look altar. Things to read are shown as
full commands, for example read sign.
